==English==
===Etymology===
Latin '''[[circumlocutio]]''', literally a speaking ([[locutio]]) around ([[circum]]).  Probably a calque of Ancient Greek '''[[περίφρασις]]''' ''(periphrasis,'' [[periphrasis]]).

===Noun===
'''circumlocution'''
#the act of talking around a subject, as to avoid it
#:''When we asked about price, the salesman launched into a lengthy '''circumlocution''' and never uttered a number.''

